'''KeePass Password Safe''' is a free [[Password manager|password management utility]] for [[Microsoft Windows]]. KeePass stores [[password]]s, usernames, and [[Uniform Resource Locator|URLs]] in an encrypted database unlocked by a password, key file, or a combination of the two. The database is encrypted with [[Advanced Encryption Standard|AES]] or [[Twofish]] encryption ciphers.
KeePass is maintained by Dominik Reichl. Development began in [[November 2003]]. The project is hosted on [[SourceForge]] and is currently rated "Production/Stable", and there are more than 28 translations available. There are currently several unofficial ports in development targeting [[Linux]], [[Mac OS X]], [[PocketPC]], and [[J2ME]].
